### =============================================================================
### LEARNING POINT: This file tests the SpecialistAgent WITHOUT an Orchestrator.
### You can see and try out A2A protocol details directly here.
### Use the VS Code "REST Client" extension or JetBrains HTTP Client.
### =============================================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5100

### -------------------------------------------
### 1. AgentCard Discovery
### LEARNING POINT: This is the FIRST step in the A2A protocol.
### Every client first fetches the AgentCard to learn:
### - What can this agent do?
### - Does it support streaming?
### - At which URL is it reachable?
### -------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/.well-known/agent-card.json
Accept: application/json

### -------------------------------------------
### 2. Health Check
### -------------------------------------------
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### -------------------------------------------
### 3. Send Message (non-streaming, JSON-RPC)
### LEARNING POINT: A2A uses JSON-RPC 2.0 as its wire format.
### The "method" determines what happens:
###   - "message/send" = synchronous response
###   - "message/sendStream" = SSE stream
### -------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/a2a/pirate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "req-001",
    "method": "message/send",
    "params": {
        "message": {
            "role": "user",
            "messageId": "msg-001",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Was ist das beste Schiff auf den sieben Meeren?"
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}

### -------------------------------------------
### 4. Streaming Message (SSE)
### LEARNING POINT: Same endpoint, but method = "message/sendStream".
### The response comes back as Server-Sent Events (SSE).
### Each token is a separate event.
### -------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/a2a/pirate
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: text/event-stream

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "req-002",
    "method": "message/sendStream",
    "params": {
        "message": {
            "role": "user",
            "messageId": "msg-002",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Erzaehl mir einen Piraten-Witz!"
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}

### -------------------------------------------
### 5. Conversation Continuity with contextId
### LEARNING POINT: Same contextId = same conversation thread.
### The agent remembers previous messages.
### -------------------------------------------
POST {{baseUrl}}/a2a/pirate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "req-003",
    "method": "message/send",
    "params": {
        "message": {
            "role": "user",
            "messageId": "msg-003",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Mein Name ist Blackbeard. Merk dir das!"
                }
            ]
        },
        "configuration": {
            "contextId": "konversation-42"
        }
    }
}

### Follow-up in the same conversation
POST {{baseUrl}}/a2a/pirate
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "jsonrpc": "2.0",
    "id": "req-004",
    "method": "message/send",
    "params": {
        "message": {
            "role": "user",
            "messageId": "msg-004",
            "parts": [
                {
                    "kind": "text",
                    "text": "Wie ist mein Name?"
                }
            ]
        },
        "configuration": {
            "contextId": "konversation-42"
        }
    }
}
